{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G4 child-consistency — container review of parent 1f19-adf2-ffb2-4b09 paired with THIS child (S6 1ba5: Docs — private-repo credentials, descriptive errors, ref/source semantics, HMAC trust model); against the WHOLE EIGHT-child roster]\n\nRan the 7 cross-child interaction modes against the WHOLE roster (S1 6d56 materialize core, S2 70c7 cache read/populate, S2b b73c janitor, S3 fa49 gate threading, S4 30b3 attested signing, S4b e308 claim-gate ref-coherence/ADR 0002, S5 b7fa CLI/MCP surfaces). All 7 modes CLEAN under the high-confidence / benign-reading filter. EMPTY G4 findings list for this pairing.\n\n1. Implicit shared state — CLEAN. Every value this docs child documents has a single named producer with a consistent producer→documenter chain: REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR + portability seam (S1); disk-cap behavior (S2 / S2b janitor); descriptive credential message+remedy (S1 AC5 raises it); ref/source + origin/main default (S3 threads, S5 surfaces); verified_at_sha + in-toto Statement shape + HMAC limits (S4, whose What delegates \"limits documented in S6\"). No documented value lacks a producer.\n\n2. Conflicting assumptions — CLEAN. Each doc claim matches the behavior: attested = pinned SHA / signs / records verified_at_sha (S4 AC1/AC2, S3 AC1); local = in-place / never signs (S3 AC4, S4 AC4); \"attested fails closed while local still runs\" (S4 AC5 unresolvable-ref fail-closed + S3 local in-place); origin/main default (S3 AC2 / S5 AC1). No contradiction.\n\n3. Dependency gap — CLEAN at this child (pure documenter; each obligation has a named producing sibling that delegates docs to S6). Checked two benign enumeration nuances, neither a high-confidence gap: (a) parent AC3's \"source=local is the DOCUMENTED back-out\" — S6 AC2/AC3 frame the local semantics; the back-out/rollback clause has a named home in S3's advisory AC (\"source=local documented as the rollback to in-place reads\"). (b) parent AC7's grace/age-window documented-defaults — S6 AC5 documents \"disk-cap behavior\"; the watermark/grace/max-age/reverify documented-defaults obligation has a named home in S2b AC9, and \"disk-cap behavior\" benignly subsumes the watermark docs. The standing S3↔S4/S4b attest.py snapshot-handle routing seam is a code-side gap that does not touch this docs child.\n\n4. Scope overlap — CLEAN. ref/source: S6 owns human PROSE (named, grep-able doc files), S5 owns inline schema-text/documented-defaults — each scoped out of the other (S5 \"Out: prose docs (S6)\"; S6 \"Out: code (S1-S5)\"). in-toto Statement: S4 BUILDS, S6 DOCUMENTS. The ADR (parent AC8) is authored code-side in S2/S2b/S4/S4b, scoped out here — no ADR-authoring overlap. S6 is the only docs child; no double-ownership of any one prose artifact.\n\n5. Ordering violation — CLEAN. The encoded graph points the benign way: S4 (30b3) and S5 (b7fa) each carry a `blocks 1ba5` edge, so the behaviors precede the docs that describe them (producer→documenter). Coherent; no contradiction. Parent AC9 only requires all-closed + green.\n\n6. Consumer impact — CLEAN. Terminal consumer/documenter; produces no API/schema/env surface a sibling depends on, so no downstream breakage. Cross-refs (alto-fruit-punch, REB-289) are out-of-epic trackers per the parent's Out-of-scope.\n\n7. Residual references — CLEAN. docs/jira-sync-setup.md (file_impact target, exists), README.md (exists; carries the MCP-setup block), REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR (S1), disk-cap (S2/S2b), EFS/NFS flock caveat xref alto-fruit-punch (matches the parent Out-of-scope), in-toto Statement (S4) all resolve. Minor benign-staleness note (NOT a finding): the body's \"Out: code (S1-S5)\" predates the roster growing to add S2b + S4b; \"code\" still resolves to all code siblings present, so no obligation is orphaned and nothing contradicts.\n\nNote (not a G4 finding on THIS pairing): the standing dependency-gap on S4 (30b3)/S4b (e308) — routing the pinned-SHA snapshot handle into plan_review/attest.py's dependency_hashes()/_rehash()/freshness re-check — is a code seam between S3/S4/S4b; it does not touch this docs child. S6 documents the HMAC trust model + ref/source semantics regardless of how that seam resolves, introducing no new inconsistency.\n\nConclusion: no high-confidence cross-child inconsistency between this Docs child and the parent/siblings. Every documented obligation maps to a named producing sibling (each delegating its docs to S6) or to an out-of-epic tracker per parent scope. EMPTY G4 findings list for this pairing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782533512869855001,"uuid":"b41f5c19-ffd2-47bf-b4c9-add9f42322ce"}